article.headline: Western Kentucky 89, Kentucky State 73
article.story: BOWLING GREEN, Ky. (AP) -- Anthony Winchester scored 21 points and Elgrace Wilborn had 14 points and 10 rebounds as Western Kentucky routed Division II Kentucky State 89-73 Wednesday night. Antonio Haynes added 15 points for the Hilltoppers (8-1), while reserves Ty Rogers and Josh Higgins had 14 and 11, respectively. Kyle Allen led Kentucky State (2-2) with 18 points, while Gerald Kuhn added 12 and Daniel Hawkins 10. Western Kentucky closed the first half with a 16-8 run over a 7-minute span that turned a 37-27 lead into a 53-35 halftime advantage. The Hilltoppers shot 51.2 percent from the field in the first half, including 7-of-11 from 3-point range. The Hilltoppers extended their lead to as many as 25 points.
